      "content": "Research suggests that higher wages can indeed benefit local economies, as increased consumer spending can boost sales and create jobs. A study by the Federal Reserve Bank of San Francisco found that every dollar increase in the minimum wage generates approximately $1.38 in additional spending in the local economy. This concept is often referred to as the \"multiplier effect,\" where increased wages ripple through the economy, benefiting businesses like yours.",
